      • registerEnvironment

        public <T extends ExternalEnvironment,U extends ListParameter<T>> void registerEnvironment(Class<T> environmentClass,
                                                                                           Class<U> listClass,
                                                                                           ExternalEnvironmentSettings settings,
                                                                                           String id,
                                                                                           String name,
                                                                                           String description,
                                                                                           Icon icon)
        Registers a new environment type. This will also register the environment class and environment list class a valid parameters. Requires that the environment class has a default constructor and a deep copy constructor. Will also register a settings page for the environment
        Type Parameters:
        T - environment class
        U - list of environment class
        Parameters:
        environmentClass - the environment class. Must be JSON-serializable. Will be registered as parameter type
        listClass - the list list. Will be registered as parameter type with ID [id]-list
        settings - Settings page that stores the user's presets
        id - the ID of the environment class. Will be used as parameter type ID
        name - the name of the environment
        description - the description of the environment
